README for the GPR library
==========================

GPR is a multi-tool C library project, open source and free to use. The goal
is to offer common functionnalities such as date manipulation, network
management and log writing. It gathers diversified features in a single,
easy to use, library.

Project content:
==================

doc/             - Auto-documentation generation
extras/          - Extra features to help development
include/         - Header files
lib/             - Library files
models/          - Model files
obj/             - Object files
src/             - Source code
tests/           - Samples to launch unitary tests

Usage:
======

GPR library:
Use the "make" utility to compile the shared library.
Use the "make install" utility with sudo privilege to install shared library on a Linux system.
Use the "make graph" utility to graph shared library dependencies. (Optional)
Use the "mahe uninstall" utility with sudo privilege to uninstall shared library from your Linux system.
Use the "make clean" utility to clean local dynamic library and object files.

tests/:
Use the "make" utility to compile tests samples.
Launch executables to see results.

External libraries usage:
=========================

- C standard library

